Heat broiler to high. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{16%ounce} into ½-inch pieces (peel first if desired).

Strip @thyme{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves.

Trim, peel, and halve @carrot{3%ounce} lengthwise; slice crosswise into ¼-inch-thick
half-moons.

Finely dice @celery{2.5%ounce}.

Halve, peel, and finely chop @yellow onion{1}.

Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Drain and return potatoes to pot. Mash with @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, @butter{1%tablespoon},
and 1 tsp chopped thyme with a #potato masher{} until smooth and creamy, adding
splashes of water as needed. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #medium, preferably
ovenproof, pan over medium-high heat.

Add carrot; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until slightly softened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Add celery, onion, and a large drizzle of oil; season with salt and pepper. Cook,
stirring, until veggies are just tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> If veggies begin to brown too quickly, add a splash of water.

Stir in garlic and 2 tsp chopped thyme; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Remove @Italian Pork Sausage{9%ounce} from casing; discard casing.

Add sausage to pan with veggies. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned
and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @flour{1%tablespoon}; cook, stirring, until thoroughly combined, ~{1%minute}.

Add ¾ cup @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce} to pan with sausage mixture. Stir in
@beef stock concentrate{1} and bring to a boil. Cook until mixture is very thick,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

> If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer filling to a #baking dish{} now.

Top sausage filling with an even layer of mashed potatoes, leaving a 1-inch border
around edge of pan.

Evenly sprinkle mashed potatoes with @white cheddar cheese{½%cup}.

Broil until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Let cool at least ~{5%minutes}, then divide between plates and serve.